cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the classification of Parkinson's disease from speech using convolutional neural networks and transfer learning. This falls under the domain of speech processing and machine learning, which are covered by several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SD (Sound) is the most likely category as it deals with speech and audio processing. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category as it deals with natural language processing, which is related to speech processing. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to classify the disease. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories as they deal with machine learning and neural networks.
